        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-23 08:16:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Also, for some reason, it doens't work for me\n > \n > $ ./oomstat -f '*requests.*' -t fancy_grid /opt/oom/kubernetes\n > Traceback (most recent call last):\n > File \"./oomstat\", line 245, in <module>\n > main()\n > File \"./oomstat\", line 227, in main\n > map(lambda p: p.keys(), projects))))\n > TypeError: reduce() of empty sequence with no initial value\n\nYou have to specify a valid path for the root directory. When using the script from the kubernetes/contrib/tools dir, the root is either the oom or kubernetes parent directory:\n$ ./oomstat -f '*requests.*' -t fancy_grid ../..\n\nBy the way the script should print a stacktrace but a human friendly message\n(fixed in commit #73406)",
        "patchset_number": 2
